♪ Have to lose ♪

24
00:01:39,710 --> 00:01:42,830
[KNOT]

25
00:01:42,970 --> 00:01:46,320
[Previously on Knot]

26
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:45,600
Let my brother go.

27
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,200
You're moving in with me.

28
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:48,360
I'll take care of you.

29
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:50,289
Nakhin told me your name's Phatsa,

30
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:51,660
which means rain.

31
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:53,600
You really smell like rain.

32
00:01:53,729 --> 00:01:56,400
I'll have Ai and Sila prepare
all the documents.

33
00:01:56,420 --> 00:01:58,000
At your service, boss.

34
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:14,360
Take a look first.

35
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:24,040
Wow.

36
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:25,350
So many?

37
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:32,200
How many decades has your company
been around?

38
00:02:32,329 --> 00:02:34,410
I only had them compile
the past three years.

39
00:02:34,410 --> 00:02:35,210
Ah.

40
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:38,700
Take a look first.

41
00:02:39,740 --> 00:02:42,300
Ask if you don't understand.

42
00:02:50,060 --> 00:02:52,430
Why are the maintenance costs in Sathorn

43
00:02:53,829 --> 00:02:56,530
so much higher than other places?

44
00:02:57,300 --> 00:02:58,900
That's a commercial area.

45
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:03,370
So to avoid business hours,

46
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:06,100
maintenance can only be done at night.

47
00:03:06,100 --> 00:03:10,790
Plus, with traffic congestion, there are
hidden costs like overtime pay.

48
00:03:11,130 --> 00:03:14,060
That's why it's more expensive
than other areas.

49
00:03:18,060 --> 00:03:18,660
OK.

50
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:20,560
If that's the case,

51
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:26,260
why are the maintenance costs in Ekkamai,
which is also downtown,
so much lower?

52
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,630
The alley we own

53
00:03:29,660 --> 00:03:31,060
is in a residential area,

54
00:03:32,130 --> 00:03:34,860
so construction can be done
during normal hours.

55
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:36,300
And over there,

56
00:03:37,100 --> 00:03:39,200
we built it as
a community commercial center,

57
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:41,160
so we can close off one section
for construction

58
00:03:41,160 --> 00:03:43,730
while keeping another section open
for business.

59
00:03:43,730 --> 00:03:45,860
They won't interfere with each other.

60
00:03:47,770 --> 00:03:48,950
I see.

61
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:57,290
I just don't quite understand.

62
00:03:58,260 --> 00:04:00,400
With the costs so high in Sathorn,

63
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:04,000
why haven't the rents increased
accordingly?

64
00:04:04,330 --> 00:04:08,760
During the day, all the shops
can operate normally

65
00:04:09,460 --> 00:04:15,130
and use the space as usual, yet both
the rent and maintenance fees here

66
00:04:15,530 --> 00:04:17,860
are about the same as Rang Nam
and Ekkamai.

67
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:21,200
I think the cost burden is too heavy here.

68
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:25,900
Mr. Phatsa is saying exactly what
Mr. Nakhun mentioned in the last meeting.

69
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:30,560
Not long ago, Mr. Nakhun also pointed out
the issue of uniform rent pricing.

70
00:04:31,130 --> 00:04:34,730
Impressive. You understood all the details
after just one look.

71
00:04:35,159 --> 00:04:38,020
And you even pointed out
the project's blind spots.

72
00:04:38,700 --> 00:04:39,900
Isn't it obvious?

73
00:04:40,159 --> 00:04:41,159
Anyone can see it.

74
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:43,600
Very impressive.

75
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:53,200
Sir.

76
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:40,000
Hello, Mr. Narate.

77
00:05:57,130 --> 00:05:59,659
Nakhin, I want to start learning
how to shoot.

78
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:01,960
I want to shoot coolly like in the movies.

79
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:04,860
If you think a gun is for looking cool,

80
00:06:05,530 --> 00:06:07,530
then I think you should just stand
and watch for now.

81
00:06:07,530 --> 00:06:08,860
I was just joking.

82
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:12,200
You can't be impatient with guns.

83
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:15,600
You must stay calm when using a gun.

84
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:19,460
Remember, when the gun is in our hands,
other people's lives are too.

85
00:06:19,660 --> 00:06:24,360
A gun is not a toy. It's not for fun
or showing off.

86
00:06:25,130 --> 00:06:26,460
Don't act on impulse.

87
00:06:27,530 --> 00:06:29,460
If you feel emotionally unstable,

88
00:06:29,930 --> 00:06:31,390
whether it's being angry,

89
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,200
irritable,

90
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:33,800
or out of control,

91
00:06:34,300 --> 00:06:36,700
stay away from guns.
As far away as possible.

92
00:06:36,700 --> 00:06:37,500
Understand?

93
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:38,320
Understood.

94
00:06:38,909 --> 00:06:39,710
Good.

95
00:06:40,330 --> 00:06:42,190
Then let's start with the basics.

96
00:06:42,530 --> 00:06:43,659
Hold the gun steady.

97
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:44,730
Stand properly.

98
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:48,430
And stop thinking about looking cool.

99
00:06:49,070 --> 00:06:52,070
Got it. Then I won't
embarrass myself today.

100
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:53,900
We'll do it another time.

101
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:58,900
Hello, Nakhun.

102
00:07:00,130 --> 00:07:00,930
Hello.

103
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:04,960
Your partner is really pretty.

104
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:06,710
Hey, it's not like that.

105
00:07:06,740 --> 00:07:07,970
Oh, really?

106
00:07:09,410 --> 00:07:10,340
No.

107
00:07:11,260 --> 00:07:12,600
Don't talk nonsense.

108
00:07:15,630 --> 00:07:17,430
He was just giving a compliment.

109
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,460
Don't join in and tease me too.

110
00:07:20,590 --> 00:07:24,510
This is a shooting range, but why does it
feel like a couple's public reveal?

111
00:07:24,510 --> 00:07:25,580
I told you it's Nakhun's partner.

112
00:07:25,580 --> 00:07:26,800
I told you no.

113
00:07:28,860 --> 00:07:32,190
Blushing like this, can you still
hold the gun steady today?

114
00:07:34,750 --> 00:07:35,830
Of course I can.

115
00:07:37,440 --> 00:07:38,590
I'm not blushing.

116
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:43,060
Still being stubborn
when you are blushing.

117
00:07:44,530 --> 00:07:46,060
Go practice your shooting.

118
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:18,260
Aim carefully.

119
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:19,300
Mm.

120
00:08:19,730 --> 00:08:22,160
Then slowly pull the trigger.

121
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:23,700
OK.

122
00:08:24,430 --> 00:08:27,560
It's a small world.
I didn't expect to run into you here.

123
00:08:28,060 --> 00:08:31,260
I didn't expect you to come
for shooting practice either.

124
00:08:32,460 --> 00:08:34,700
People need some self-defense skills.

125
00:08:35,370 --> 00:08:38,570
Especially with the news
being so lively lately.

126
00:08:40,830 --> 00:08:48,290
I heard the eldest son of the Devathitirat
family bit an Omega's neck.

127
00:08:48,560 --> 00:08:52,760
And a helpless Omega at that.

128
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:58,800
Phatsa is not helpless.

129
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:01,430
It seems he is very special to you.

130
00:09:01,430 --> 00:09:03,020
Of course.

131
00:09:03,900 --> 00:09:06,390
Much more special than most people.

132
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:09,740
Then I should get to know him.

133
00:09:09,930 --> 00:09:16,440
See what kind of person makes a True Alpha
so protective.

134
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:19,130
I am...

135
00:09:19,730 --> 00:09:20,830
Amintra.

136
00:09:21,030 --> 00:09:22,160
Nice to meet you.

137
00:09:38,530 --> 00:09:39,430
I'm Phatsa.

138
00:09:42,700 --> 00:09:45,930
Do you know how to shoot?
How about a competition?

139
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:48,060
Miss Amintra...

140
00:09:48,460 --> 00:09:50,760
Uh, that's not necessary...

141
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:51,760
Enough.

142
00:09:53,030 --> 00:09:55,230
This is not a place for a game of dare.

143
00:09:58,500 --> 00:09:59,530
Or are you afraid?

144
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:03,660
Sure. I can do that.

145
00:10:04,260 --> 00:10:05,460
Miss Amintra.

146
00:10:06,330 --> 00:10:07,130
Phatsa.

147
00:10:08,330 --> 00:10:09,660
If you want to compete,

148
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:12,360
I'm happy to keep you company

149
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:15,660
and relieve your boredom.

150
00:10:16,370 --> 00:10:17,170
Good.

151
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:19,660
I like that you don't back down.

152
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:23,160
I like it too.

153
00:11:20,460 --> 00:11:21,660
You are very skilled.

154
00:11:22,030 --> 00:11:24,700
I concede this shooting match.

155
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:25,960
You win.

156
00:11:26,530 --> 00:11:28,390
You gave up faster than I thought.

157
00:11:28,460 --> 00:11:30,920
A loss is a loss.
No need to put on a brave face.

158
00:11:31,150 --> 00:11:34,750
What a pity. I thought you could
let me have more fun.

159
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:38,200
I'm not here to spoil the fun.

160
00:11:40,130 --> 00:11:41,660
Well said, sister-in-law.

161
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:48,920
Forget it, today is boring.
Let's go, Kingyok.

162
00:11:49,790 --> 00:11:50,590
OK.

163
00:11:54,020 --> 00:11:58,750
Hope we can play something
more interesting next time.

164
00:12:08,860 --> 00:12:10,990
I thought you two would really go at it.

165
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:13,130
This is enough.

166
00:12:13,660 --> 00:12:15,260
At least it ended well today.

167
00:12:17,060 --> 00:12:18,860
I'm going to the restroom first.

168
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:20,880
Sila, you go with Phatsa.

169
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:21,420
OK.

170
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:22,900
No need.

171
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:40,000
Phatsa shot this.

172
00:12:41,660 --> 00:12:42,960
Nice shooting.

173
00:12:43,700 --> 00:12:45,630
At least he didn't miss the target.

174
00:12:48,730 --> 00:12:49,660
What's wrong?

175
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,760
Phatsa didn't shoot to score.

176
00:12:54,260 --> 00:12:55,360
What do you mean?

177
00:12:56,090 --> 00:12:58,770
This shot
is to disarm the opponent.

178
00:12:59,330 --> 00:13:02,420
This shot is to restrict their movement.

179
00:13:03,160 --> 00:13:04,000
This shot...

180
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,060
is to end the fight.

181
00:13:09,330 --> 00:13:10,700
As for this top shot,

182
00:13:11,560 --> 00:13:12,700
if it hit,

183
00:13:14,730 --> 00:13:15,800
it would be fatal.

184
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:20,000
Phatsa didn't aim at the bullseye
to score.

185
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:23,230
But he fought back immediately
upon picking up the gun,

186
00:13:23,230 --> 00:13:25,500
as if his body instinctively knew

187
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:29,330
where to hit to stop the enemy instantly.

188
00:13:30,260 --> 00:13:32,300
Like shooting in actual combat.

189
00:13:33,930 --> 00:13:34,730
Mm.

190
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:38,730
But Phatsa looks like someone
who has never practiced shooting.

191
00:13:38,730 --> 00:13:40,660
That's what makes it interesting.

192
00:13:41,160 --> 00:13:42,290
That's an instinct.

193
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:46,630
Not an instinct that an ordinary shooter
would have.

194
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:53,630
But an instinct that only someone
who knows how to kill a target would have.

195
00:13:54,860 --> 00:14:01,000
At least he knows what to do
to stop the target instantly.

196
00:14:04,060 --> 00:14:05,930
So, he's quite formidable.

197
00:14:06,610 --> 00:14:09,690
Yes, quite formidable.

198
00:14:11,060 --> 00:14:18,530
If so, it seems many interesting things
will happen in the future.

199
00:14:21,100 --> 00:14:21,900
Yeah.

200
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:47,560
Is Phatsa here, Ongsa?

201
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:49,290
He's not here today.

202
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:54,930
He didn't answer my calls
or read my messages.

203
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:02,660
Phatsa must be quite busy lately.

204
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,260
I heard he moved in with someone else.

205
00:15:08,030 --> 00:15:08,830
Hmm...

206
00:15:09,220 --> 00:15:10,020
Really?

207
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:14,490
I wanted to invite Phatsa to a movie.

208
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:18,030
Isn't it almost time to be in Heat?

209
00:15:20,950 --> 00:15:24,310
I think it's safer to stay at home.

210
00:15:25,450 --> 00:15:33,130
Yeah, but I'm wearing a collar,
so it should be fine, right?

211
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:41,200
And it's safe if Phatsa's with me,
isn't it?

212
00:15:43,220 --> 00:15:44,420
Is it really safe?

213
00:15:45,700 --> 00:15:48,600
Of course, because Phatsa

214
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:52,580
could be an Alpha, right?

215
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:55,230
You misunderstood.

216
00:15:57,360 --> 00:15:58,760
Phatsa's an Omega.

217
00:16:00,180 --> 00:16:00,980
What?

218
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:04,530
That's what the test results say.

219
00:16:06,100 --> 00:16:08,190
How is he doing now then?

220
00:16:09,170 --> 00:16:10,830
I heard

221
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:14,600
he has already formed a bond.

222
00:16:15,930 --> 00:16:17,960
Has he really formed a bond?

223
00:16:40,530 --> 00:16:41,500
Mr. Phatsa.

224
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:42,960
I didn't order this, did I?

225
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:46,450
Mr. Nakhun ordered us
to prepare this for you.

226
00:16:47,450 --> 00:16:49,110
Enjoy your meal.

227
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:50,100
Thank you.

228
00:16:50,140 --> 00:16:51,180
Please eat.

229
00:16:51,550 --> 00:16:52,790
Aren't you coming in?

230
00:16:52,970 --> 00:16:55,640
We need to watch you finish the meal.

231
00:16:56,700 --> 00:16:57,930
I can do it myself.

232
00:16:57,950 --> 00:17:00,220
No, these are Mr. Nakhun's orders.

233
00:17:16,150 --> 00:17:17,260
Sir.

234
00:17:17,750 --> 00:17:18,930
It's fine.

235
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:19,630
No.

236
00:17:19,730 --> 00:17:20,329
Don't.

237
00:17:20,910 --> 00:17:22,060
Don't move.

238
00:17:22,079 --> 00:17:23,970
Sir, I can't get it on you like this.

239
00:17:23,970 --> 00:17:25,040
Sorry.

240
00:17:27,060 --> 00:17:28,349
Put it on properly.

241
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,600
Do you want to play together?

242
00:17:37,050 --> 00:17:37,890
Mr. Phatsa.

243
00:17:38,630 --> 00:17:41,160
Mr. Nakhun has asked me
to prepare the meal.

244
00:17:41,340 --> 00:17:42,560
Please go eat first.

245
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:47,500
You have an online meeting this afternoon.

246
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:50,730
I have put the materials in the study.

247
00:17:51,190 --> 00:17:51,990
OK.

248
00:17:57,360 --> 00:17:59,690
Mr. Phatsa hasn't come down
for a meal yet.

249
00:18:02,060 --> 00:18:02,860
OK.

250
00:18:10,300 --> 00:18:11,900
Why didn't you go down to eat?

251
00:18:12,130 --> 00:18:13,100
I'm not hungry.

252
00:18:13,490 --> 00:18:15,330
You have to eat even if you're not hungry.

253
00:18:15,330 --> 00:18:17,000
It's not good to keep everyone

254
00:18:17,330 --> 00:18:19,060
waiting for the meal, you know?

255
00:18:20,130 --> 00:18:21,590
But I don't know what to do.

256
00:18:22,700 --> 00:18:24,900
I'm bored to death staying here all day.

257
00:18:25,460 --> 00:18:27,990
And someone has to drive me
every time I go out.

258
00:18:29,160 --> 00:18:30,490
When you're not around,

259
00:18:33,530 --> 00:18:36,790
I don't even know how to cope with
being in this empty house.

260
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:38,560
Here,

261
00:18:39,760 --> 00:18:41,360
you can do whatever you want.

262
00:18:42,260 --> 00:18:46,500
Didn't I tell you?
I will give you everything you want.

263
00:18:47,930 --> 00:18:48,730
But...

264
00:18:51,260 --> 00:18:52,660
You are so busy with work.

265
00:18:54,260 --> 00:18:56,920
But I will still make time
for important things.

266
00:18:59,460 --> 00:19:00,600
Let's go eat now.

267
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:02,560
I'm hungry.

268
00:20:07,020 --> 00:20:07,820
Nakhun.

269
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:13,100
How much longer do I have to stay here?

270
00:20:19,210 --> 00:20:22,140
Maybe for a lifetime.

271
00:21:20,060 --> 00:21:21,160
I used to think...

272
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:25,500
That after I graduate,

273
00:21:27,060 --> 00:21:28,800
I would find a good job,

274
00:21:30,930 --> 00:21:32,100
work hard,

275
00:21:33,660 --> 00:21:35,530
live the life I want,

276
00:21:39,320 --> 00:21:44,460
and go everywhere I want to go.

277
00:21:46,330 --> 00:21:47,130
I'm sorry.

278
00:21:51,500 --> 00:21:59,430
Making this bond is no different
from being tied up in chains.

279
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:08,460
It's like a dead knot
trapping me constantly.

280
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:21,300
If this continues, one day...

281
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:24,500
I will die of sorrow.

282
00:22:26,330 --> 00:22:27,700
I won't let that happen.

283
00:22:58,760 --> 00:23:00,200
Where are you taking me?

284
00:23:00,580 --> 00:23:01,380
Nowhere.

285
00:23:13,360 --> 00:23:14,160
Whose is this?

286
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:16,000
Yours.

287
00:23:18,560 --> 00:23:19,530
Mine?

288
00:23:20,130 --> 00:23:23,140
Yesterday you said you didn't want to

289
00:23:23,140 --> 00:23:26,160
bother the driver every time you went out.

290
00:23:37,860 --> 00:23:39,160
I can't accept it.

291
00:23:40,900 --> 00:23:42,030
It's too expensive.

292
00:23:47,560 --> 00:23:48,960
This car is a gift for you.

293
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:51,460
All the paperwork is in your name.

294
00:23:53,060 --> 00:23:53,860
But...

295
00:23:57,530 --> 00:23:58,800
I don't want it.

296
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:07,260
If you don't want it, you can leave it
parked, or sell it. Whatever you want.

297
00:24:41,130 --> 00:24:41,930
Hey.

298
00:24:55,460 --> 00:24:56,390
Are you mad at me?

299
00:24:57,500 --> 00:24:59,160
I just wanted to buy it for you.

300
00:24:59,930 --> 00:25:01,930
If accepting it feels like a burden,

301
00:25:03,860 --> 00:25:04,960
just throw it away.

302
00:25:10,530 --> 00:25:12,130
It's not that I don't want it.

303
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:15,690
It's just that the things you give
are too expensive.

304
00:25:19,330 --> 00:25:23,100
Didn't I say I'd give you everything?

305
00:25:27,730 --> 00:25:29,190
Are you working tomorrow?

306
00:25:29,900 --> 00:25:31,360
Do you want me to drive you?

307
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:33,330
My company is very far away.

308
00:25:34,040 --> 00:25:37,290
I'm a very good driver.

309
00:25:38,160 --> 00:25:39,600
Do you have a license?

310
00:25:40,620 --> 00:25:41,420
Of course I do.

311
00:25:45,900 --> 00:25:47,230
Are you not mad anymore?

312
00:25:48,120 --> 00:25:50,790
I wasn't mad in the first place.

313
00:26:34,900 --> 00:26:35,830
The car is dirty.

314
00:26:36,600 --> 00:26:39,460
Let's go check out
the Rangsit warehouse tomorrow.

315
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:41,800
I want you to see the actual site.

316
00:26:42,900 --> 00:26:43,960
I can go too?

317
00:26:45,060 --> 00:26:47,060
Didn't you want to help me with work?

318
00:26:49,660 --> 00:26:55,030
Of course, boss.
Just tell me, I'll do anything. But...

319
00:26:55,560 --> 00:26:57,000
Can you afford it?

320
00:26:57,930 --> 00:26:59,130
Then name your price.

321
00:27:00,300 --> 00:27:03,070
What's your minimum salary?

322
00:27:03,660 --> 00:27:06,930
As my assistant, about 30,000.

323
00:27:09,300 --> 00:27:10,330
But if it's you...

324
00:27:13,250 --> 00:27:14,410
Is 300,000 enough?

325
00:27:14,440 --> 00:27:15,630
300,000?

326
00:27:16,550 --> 00:27:17,480
Is it too little?

327
00:27:19,360 --> 00:27:20,260
Or 500,000?

328
00:27:21,730 --> 00:27:23,930
At 30,000, I was ready to latch onto you.

329
00:27:24,600 --> 00:27:25,530
300,000, deal.

330
00:27:33,010 --> 00:27:35,340
Someone has already bought it.

331
00:27:59,500 --> 00:28:00,300
Phatsa.

332
00:28:52,200 --> 00:28:53,360
Smells so good.

333
00:29:41,820 --> 00:29:47,180
I think if this place is transformed into
a creative space,

334
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:51,500
or a rental studio, it would be
more suitable.

335
00:29:52,250 --> 00:29:53,050
You

336
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:56,160
always manage to impress me.

337
00:29:56,900 --> 00:29:59,300
Didn't I tell you? I really want to work.

338
00:30:14,960 --> 00:30:16,660
I'll go take a call.

339
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:19,000
Ai,

340
00:30:19,600 --> 00:30:21,100
I'll leave Phatsa in your care.

341
00:30:21,100 --> 00:30:21,900
OK.

342
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:28,420
Do you want to keep looking around?

343
00:30:28,420 --> 00:30:29,220
Sure.

344
00:30:32,200 --> 00:30:32,800
Hello.

345
00:30:33,330 --> 00:30:34,730
I'm at the warehouse now.

346
00:30:35,900 --> 00:30:37,360
It'll probably be a while.

347
00:30:44,660 --> 00:30:46,190
There's so much stuff here.

348
00:30:48,860 --> 00:30:50,600
What was this place used for before?

349
00:30:50,600 --> 00:30:52,930
It was probably a warehouse.

350
00:30:55,590 --> 00:30:56,390
Hey!

351
00:30:56,660 --> 00:30:57,130
Ah!

352
00:30:57,130 --> 00:30:58,160
Phatsa!

353
00:30:58,960 --> 00:30:59,760
Mr. Nakhun!

354
00:31:00,820 --> 00:31:02,110
Mr. Nakhun!

355
00:31:02,200 --> 00:31:02,730
Mr. Nakhun!

356
00:31:02,730 --> 00:31:03,900
What happened?

357
00:31:03,990 --> 00:31:05,070
Mr. Nakhun!

358
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:09,260
Mr. Nakhun!

359
00:31:09,710 --> 00:31:12,030
Stay with me! Are you OK?

360
00:31:12,860 --> 00:31:13,790
Phatsa.

361
00:31:15,230 --> 00:31:15,700
Phatsa.

362
00:31:20,240 --> 00:31:21,510
Stay with me!

363
00:31:21,530 --> 00:31:22,450
Are you OK?

364
00:31:23,990 --> 00:31:24,520
Phatsa.

365
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:25,660
Mr. Nakhun.

366
00:31:25,680 --> 00:31:26,480
Slow down.

367
00:31:26,510 --> 00:31:27,310
Phatsa.

368
00:31:27,560 --> 00:31:28,400
Mr. Nakhun.

369
00:31:30,170 --> 00:31:31,000
Phatsa.

370
00:31:31,870 --> 00:31:32,870
Ah, easy!

371
00:31:34,030 --> 00:31:34,930
Be careful.

372
00:31:40,470 --> 00:31:41,710
Easy.

373
00:31:42,760 --> 00:31:44,720
-Ah!
-Slow down.

374
00:31:55,330 --> 00:31:56,200
Can you walk?

375
00:32:09,900 --> 00:32:10,830
How do you feel?

376
00:32:11,180 --> 00:32:12,630
It's safe now.

377
00:32:14,360 --> 00:32:15,690
I'll take my leave then.

378
00:32:16,160 --> 00:32:17,220
Thank you, doctor.

379
00:32:30,460 --> 00:32:32,660
Are you OK?

380
00:32:34,300 --> 00:32:35,800
Why are you so pale?

381
00:32:38,160 --> 00:32:38,960
I'm fine.

382
00:32:45,860 --> 00:32:47,990
When I saw you standing there just now,

383
00:32:50,660 --> 00:32:52,720
my heart really felt like it stopped.

384
00:32:54,500 --> 00:32:55,860
But I'm right here now.

385
00:32:59,010 --> 00:33:00,890
And everything is fine.

386
00:33:08,960 --> 00:33:10,000
Are you sure?

387
00:33:12,110 --> 00:33:14,520
How did you get into an accident outside?

388
00:33:15,760 --> 00:33:16,760
Does it hurt, kid?

389
00:33:17,190 --> 00:33:17,990
Ouch,

390
00:33:18,020 --> 00:33:19,170
a little bit.

391
00:33:20,820 --> 00:33:22,190
Where are you hurt? Where?

392
00:33:22,190 --> 00:33:23,970
Oh, you scared me to death!

393
00:33:25,060 --> 00:33:26,600
Thank you, Ms. Kampirada.

394
00:33:28,250 --> 00:33:31,570
Didn't I tell you? Call me Mom.

395
00:33:32,230 --> 00:33:33,030
Uh...

396
00:33:34,330 --> 00:33:35,160
OK, Mom.

397
00:33:37,860 --> 00:33:38,710
You...

398
00:33:39,360 --> 00:33:43,000
Nakhun, how could you take him out
and get into an accident?

399
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:45,380
Why didn't you take good care of him?

400
00:33:45,490 --> 00:33:49,060
No, Mom. It's not his fault.

401
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:53,360
I usually heal quickly from injuries.

402
00:33:58,330 --> 00:33:59,660
Oh, it must hurt a lot.

403
00:34:03,230 --> 00:34:05,460
If you can't even take care of yourself
with this little thing,

404
00:34:05,460 --> 00:34:07,590
then you shouldn't do anything at all!

405
00:34:07,600 --> 00:34:09,530
This little injury won't kill him.

406
00:34:10,080 --> 00:34:12,340
What's wrong with this family?

407
00:34:12,520 --> 00:34:14,699
Instead of doing your own business,

408
00:34:15,110 --> 00:34:18,510
you're hovering around a
helpless Omega!

409
00:34:31,900 --> 00:34:33,110
We have a problem.

410
00:34:33,560 --> 00:34:37,199
Our bar in Thonglor
was raided by the police for drugs.

411
00:34:37,730 --> 00:34:38,860
How did this happen?

412
00:34:39,159 --> 00:34:41,300
Mr. Naphitch was there at the time.

413
00:34:41,800 --> 00:34:44,770
He's been taken to the police station.

414
00:34:45,110 --> 00:34:45,909
What?

415
00:34:50,460 --> 00:34:52,120
Wasn't it already inspected?

416
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:09,860
Hello, Mr. Nakhun.

417
00:35:10,860 --> 00:35:12,120
What's the situation?

418
00:35:12,130 --> 00:35:15,800
According to the preliminary urine test,
Mr. Naphitch tested negative for drugs.

419
00:35:15,800 --> 00:35:17,300
However, the reason he's still here

420
00:35:17,300 --> 00:35:19,800
is because he got into a fight
with the bar owner.

421
00:35:19,800 --> 00:35:21,680
That bastard deserved to be beaten,
didn't he?

422
00:35:21,680 --> 00:35:22,450
Hey,

423
00:35:22,600 --> 00:35:23,800
calm down first.

424
00:35:23,840 --> 00:35:26,760
Calm down? I didn't do anything wrong!

425
00:35:27,500 --> 00:35:29,300
Let's talk this through calmly.

426
00:35:33,060 --> 00:35:34,760
It's good that nothing came up.

427
00:35:34,760 --> 00:35:35,560
Nakhin,

428
00:35:36,130 --> 00:35:37,560
take Naphitch to the car.

429
00:35:37,750 --> 00:35:38,880
I'm not going.

430
00:35:40,100 --> 00:35:42,150
I'm not leaving until I beat that bastard

431
00:35:42,150 --> 00:35:43,510
until he spits blood!

432
00:35:44,200 --> 00:35:45,860
I've kept him for nothing.

433
00:35:46,500 --> 00:35:48,130
Leave this to me.

434
00:35:50,760 --> 00:35:51,890
Let's go first, bro.

435
00:35:52,200 --> 00:35:53,860
We'll talk in the car. Get up!

436
00:36:30,850 --> 00:36:32,160
Listen to me first.

437
00:36:32,560 --> 00:36:34,160
Did you put drugs in my bar?

438
00:36:36,260 --> 00:36:37,060
I...

439
00:36:37,330 --> 00:36:38,330
I had no choice.

440
00:36:39,530 --> 00:36:42,100
That place was originally
your family's property.

441
00:36:42,100 --> 00:36:43,960
After the mortgage was released,

442
00:36:44,330 --> 00:36:45,860
I bought it back.

443
00:36:47,260 --> 00:36:49,100
I opened a bar on that land

444
00:36:50,780 --> 00:36:53,040
not because I wanted to do more business,

445
00:36:53,960 --> 00:36:56,690
but because I wanted to leave you
a place to stand.

446
00:36:57,960 --> 00:36:59,240
I wanted you to come back and take over

447
00:36:59,240 --> 00:37:01,700
the place that once
belonged to your family.

448
00:37:01,860 --> 00:37:03,260
I know you're helping me.

449
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:04,760
I know.

450
00:37:04,860 --> 00:37:05,720
I never forgot.

451
00:37:06,460 --> 00:37:07,260
You know what?

452
00:37:07,970 --> 00:37:10,020
You didn't just ruin yourself.

453
00:37:11,400 --> 00:37:13,530
You ruined your family's reputation.

454
00:37:13,960 --> 00:37:16,160
And you ruined my trust in you.

455
00:37:38,260 --> 00:37:39,760
Why are you so impulsive?

456
00:37:42,910 --> 00:37:44,010
So boring.

457
00:37:45,160 --> 00:37:46,360
Bro, what do you know?

458
00:38:16,900 --> 00:38:18,000
You're back.

459
00:38:20,060 --> 00:38:21,190
Why are you still up?

460
00:38:27,660 --> 00:38:28,860
I was waiting for you.

461
00:39:05,540 --> 00:39:06,340
Are you tired?

462
00:39:10,780 --> 00:39:11,770
A little bit.

463
00:39:17,660 --> 00:39:18,720
Then get some rest.

464
00:39:37,300 --> 00:39:39,030
I can't help you with anything,

465
00:39:41,160 --> 00:39:43,090
but at least I can keep you company.

466
00:39:43,800 --> 00:39:44,800
Then may I hug you?

467
00:39:44,970 --> 00:39:46,130
No.

468
00:39:47,730 --> 00:39:49,060
Didn't I tell you not to?

469
00:39:50,600 --> 00:39:52,400
But you're hugging me right now.

470
00:39:57,430 --> 00:39:58,230
Oh.

471
00:40:00,340 --> 00:40:01,670
I'm not hugging you.

472
00:40:01,700 --> 00:40:02,900
It's just a touch.

473
00:40:04,380 --> 00:40:05,180
Hmm.

474
00:40:10,340 --> 00:40:13,550
You're so bad. Aren't you tired?

475
00:40:13,550 --> 00:40:16,770
Go take a shower first.
You'll feel better.

476
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:22,460
I'm going to take a shower.

477
00:40:43,800 --> 00:40:46,330
I just realized how tiring it is
to be an Omega.

478
00:40:46,800 --> 00:40:48,760
Not only does your body change,

479
00:40:49,700 --> 00:40:51,760
but your freedom is also restricted.

480
00:40:52,330 --> 00:40:54,130
It's just like being a prisoner.

481
00:40:54,460 --> 00:40:55,260
Well.

482
00:40:55,930 --> 00:40:57,530
You've already been bitten.

483
00:40:58,100 --> 00:40:59,500
And the one who bit you

484
00:41:00,100 --> 00:41:02,130
is a True Alpha.

485
00:41:04,460 --> 00:41:06,060
Just bear with it for now.

486
00:41:07,130 --> 00:41:08,990
Once your pheromones stabilize,

487
00:41:09,460 --> 00:41:11,320
things should slowly get better.

488
00:41:13,760 --> 00:41:15,820
Oh, Phatsa, Ongsa,

489
00:41:16,590 --> 00:41:17,920
everyone is here today.

490
00:41:18,500 --> 00:41:20,960
Are you guys talking about
something serious?

491
00:41:20,960 --> 00:41:24,330
It's just Phatsa
complaining about his life as an Omega.

492
00:41:25,500 --> 00:41:30,400
That's normal, Phatsa.
Being an Omega in an Alpha-dominated world

493
00:41:30,400 --> 00:41:35,140
is not easy.
Let me, the expert, give you a lesson.

494
00:41:35,700 --> 00:41:37,900
I'll teach you how to use your instincts,

495
00:41:37,900 --> 00:41:39,430
what to be careful of,

496
00:41:39,900 --> 00:41:42,160
and how you can control Alphas instead.

497
00:41:43,800 --> 00:41:44,860
You can count on it.

498
00:41:46,060 --> 00:41:51,660
Since you're being my expert,
about being bitten,

499
00:41:53,100 --> 00:41:54,960
is there any way to get back at him?

500
00:41:55,930 --> 00:41:57,390
Speaking of being bitten,

501
00:41:57,800 --> 00:42:00,160
I really want to meet that Alpha.

502
00:42:00,530 --> 00:42:01,860
His character is so bad.

503
00:42:02,930 --> 00:42:04,530
You barely knew each other,

504
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:06,630
and he bit you already.

505
00:42:06,760 --> 00:42:08,290
These Alphas

506
00:42:08,800 --> 00:42:10,210
are all the same.

507
00:42:10,930 --> 00:42:13,330
They always trust their beastly instincts

508
00:42:13,860 --> 00:42:15,710
more than their brains.

509
00:42:16,200 --> 00:42:17,570
That's true.

510
00:42:18,130 --> 00:42:18,930
However,

511
00:42:19,800 --> 00:42:22,600
you can't entirely blame them
for losing control.

512
00:42:23,130 --> 00:42:25,560
Phatsa, are you defending them?

513
00:42:25,760 --> 00:42:28,840
No, I'm not.

514
00:42:30,460 --> 00:42:33,060
Since I got bitten, he's been
really good to me.

515
00:42:34,930 --> 00:42:39,060
So good that I almost forgot
he took away my freedom.

516
00:42:40,200 --> 00:42:42,200
Taking good care of you is one thing,

517
00:42:43,400 --> 00:42:46,130
but ruining a rare breed like us

518
00:42:46,600 --> 00:42:48,100
is really hard to forgive.

519
00:42:49,760 --> 00:42:53,500
But let's not talk about Alphas anymore.

520
00:42:54,360 --> 00:42:55,800
I'm hungry.

521
00:42:57,130 --> 00:43:00,960
Let's order some food. It's on me.

522
00:43:02,200 --> 00:43:07,730
Let's treat it as a celebration for Phatsa
dodging that falling beam.

523
00:43:11,400 --> 00:43:16,100
Speaking of that piece of wood,
it really hurt when it first hit me.

524
00:43:17,660 --> 00:43:23,460
But it got better quickly.
Later, it hardly hurt at all.

525
00:43:26,530 --> 00:43:30,760
Is that some special Alpha-Omega trait?

526
00:43:32,660 --> 00:43:35,130
But I've never heard of it either.

527
00:43:40,530 --> 00:43:43,860
Could it be that you are
that type of Omega,

528
00:43:45,160 --> 00:43:47,500
so your body recovers faster than normal?

529
00:43:58,460 --> 00:43:59,260
Let's eat.

530
00:44:00,600 --> 00:44:01,800
Phatsa.

531
00:44:03,260 --> 00:44:05,790
The car is already waiting for you
at the door.

532
00:44:08,530 --> 00:44:11,590
What the hell? I've been here
only for less than an hour.

533
00:44:12,300 --> 00:44:16,360
Mr. Nakhun specifically instructed
that you shouldn't stay out too long

534
00:44:16,700 --> 00:44:19,360
because he's worried about the injury
on your arm.

535
00:44:19,360 --> 00:44:24,560
And it seems Mr. Nakhun still cares a lot
about the warehouse accident.

536
00:44:25,960 --> 00:44:27,130
He has a point.

537
00:44:27,460 --> 00:44:30,190
I just heard Phatsa saying
the wound was itching.

538
00:44:30,460 --> 00:44:31,820
Go home and rest.

539
00:44:32,200 --> 00:44:34,000
Bro, why are you taking his side?

540
00:44:34,600 --> 00:44:36,390
Go back and tell your boss

541
00:44:36,730 --> 00:44:38,330
to give me another half hour.

542
00:44:39,260 --> 00:44:41,860
Let me finish dinner
with my friends first, OK?

543
00:44:42,060 --> 00:44:44,760
I'll go back as soon as I finish.
I promise I won't run off.

544
00:44:44,760 --> 00:44:45,930
But Mr. Nakhun...

545
00:44:45,960 --> 00:44:51,100
Just tell him if he doesn't let me finish
my meal, I'm not coming home at all.

546
00:44:51,800 --> 00:44:52,600
OK.

547
00:44:53,760 --> 00:44:54,930
Oh my, Phatsa,

548
00:44:55,760 --> 00:44:58,460
you even have bodyguards watching you
all the way.

549
00:44:58,460 --> 00:45:02,060
I don't know if he's worried
about the wound or worried about you.

550
00:45:02,500 --> 00:45:03,300
Saengnuea...

551
00:45:04,860 --> 00:45:06,570
I'm just joking.

552
00:45:07,100 --> 00:45:09,300
He's so worried that he's going insane.

553
00:45:12,550 --> 00:45:13,350
Bro.

554
00:45:14,330 --> 00:45:15,900
Hand me the drink menu.

555
00:45:19,200 --> 00:45:21,800
I'm thirsty. I want to have
four or five drinks.

556
00:45:23,000 --> 00:45:24,930
I'll wait for your order at the bar.

557
00:45:25,660 --> 00:45:26,460
Five drinks.

558
00:45:32,600 --> 00:45:34,000
What do you want to drink?

559
00:45:34,960 --> 00:45:36,020
You can order, bro.

560
00:45:37,130 --> 00:45:38,260
Do you want anything?

561
00:45:38,260 --> 00:45:39,060
No, thanks.

562
00:45:39,660 --> 00:45:40,800
Saves me some money.

563
00:45:43,040 --> 00:45:44,440
I'll have a glass of this.

564
00:45:45,240 --> 00:45:45,910
This one.

565
00:45:46,200 --> 00:45:47,000
And...

566
00:45:47,730 --> 00:45:48,530
This one.

567
00:45:49,160 --> 00:45:50,360
This one and this one.

568
00:45:50,800 --> 00:45:51,200
This one.

569
00:45:51,200 --> 00:45:51,600
Right.

570
00:45:52,300 --> 00:45:53,100
Another cup.

571
00:45:53,700 --> 00:45:54,500
Four drinks.

572
00:45:56,160 --> 00:45:56,690
This one.

573
00:45:56,860 --> 00:45:57,460
No way.

574
00:45:58,360 --> 00:46:02,760
Oh, Primprao. Do you want donuts today?

575
00:46:02,950 --> 00:46:05,020
Yes. Are there any left?

576
00:46:05,160 --> 00:46:07,540
Yes, a moment please.

577
00:46:07,730 --> 00:46:08,530
OK.

578
00:46:12,260 --> 00:46:15,130
Bro, can I ask you a question?

579
00:46:16,160 --> 00:46:18,500
Sure.

580
00:46:19,190 --> 00:46:23,010
Is it weird if I haven't gotten
my secondary gender tested yet?

581
00:46:24,260 --> 00:46:26,160
Not at all.

582
00:46:27,860 --> 00:46:29,350
Why do you ask all of a sudden?

583
00:46:29,350 --> 00:46:35,230
My family keeps saying they're waiting
to see what I'll present as.

584
00:46:35,460 --> 00:46:40,560
So I was thinking, if the result isn't
what they hope for,

585
00:46:40,700 --> 00:46:42,800
will I still be the same me?

586
00:46:44,060 --> 00:46:45,120
Of course you will.

587
00:46:46,600 --> 00:46:53,490
Whether you're an Alpha, a Beta,
or an Omega,

588
00:46:54,460 --> 00:46:56,660
you're still a human being, aren't you?

589
00:46:57,260 --> 00:46:58,060
Really?

590
00:46:59,500 --> 00:47:00,130
Of course.

591
00:47:01,330 --> 00:47:06,560
But more importantly, it's about
what kind of person we become.

592
00:47:07,930 --> 00:47:11,900
Not what the test results say we are.
Don't overthink it.

593
00:47:13,760 --> 00:47:15,660
Primprao, your donuts are ready.

594
00:47:15,680 --> 00:47:16,560
Thank you.

595
00:47:17,400 --> 00:47:18,560
And thank you, bro.

596
00:47:18,760 --> 00:47:19,560
Mm.

597
00:47:19,800 --> 00:47:21,260
Take your time growing up.

598
00:47:27,300 --> 00:47:28,630
The drinks are ordered.

599
00:47:29,800 --> 00:47:31,000
Let's eat.

600
00:47:43,200 --> 00:47:45,510
Sister-in-law, Brother has
a last-minute meeting,

601
00:47:45,510 --> 00:47:47,830
so he asked me to take over.

602
00:47:48,900 --> 00:47:51,410
He was afraid leaving a beauty outside
for too long

603
00:47:51,410 --> 00:47:53,930
would attract moths
and infect your wounds.

604
00:47:55,200 --> 00:47:57,200
Didn't I tell you not to call me that?

605
00:47:57,330 --> 00:48:02,660
And what's with that guy, sending people
to watch me endlessly?

606
00:48:04,000 --> 00:48:07,800
So, did you like the flowers
I sent to the shop?

607
00:48:10,860 --> 00:48:12,060
What flowers?

608
00:48:13,360 --> 00:48:16,100
Or did something happen
that I don't know about?

609
00:48:19,100 --> 00:48:20,360
Have you eaten?

610
00:48:21,400 --> 00:48:22,200
Come.

611
00:48:22,800 --> 00:48:23,600
Phatsa.

612
00:48:24,050 --> 00:48:25,450
Mr. Nakhin must be busy.

613
00:48:25,470 --> 00:48:26,870
And I happen to be hungry.

614
00:48:28,160 --> 00:48:34,700
Hungry and free, I won't hold back then.

615
00:48:35,660 --> 00:48:38,500
Eat up, these are all Ongsa's favorites.

616
00:48:42,460 --> 00:48:45,530
Hello, I'm Saengnuea.

617
00:48:46,360 --> 00:48:50,030
Are you an Alpha?

618
00:48:50,930 --> 00:48:52,400
I can smell your pheromone.

619
00:48:52,400 --> 00:48:53,530
Hello, Saengnuea.

620
00:48:55,500 --> 00:48:58,400
With this scent, you must be an Omega.

621
00:48:59,300 --> 00:49:00,060
Yes.

622
00:49:00,060 --> 00:49:04,260
It's rare to see an Omega as pretty as you
with such a nice pheromone scent.

623
00:49:08,760 --> 00:49:10,020
You are really pretty.

624
00:49:13,500 --> 00:49:14,300
Ongsa.

625
00:49:15,730 --> 00:49:17,360
What's wrong? You look pale.

626
00:49:18,530 --> 00:49:23,900
Nothing, this food is just too bland.

627
00:49:25,330 --> 00:49:26,260
I'm full.

628
00:49:27,200 --> 00:49:28,660
Come again next time, bro.

629
00:49:30,730 --> 00:49:34,700
Saengnuea, teach me more about Omegas
next time.

630
00:49:34,960 --> 00:49:38,330
I'll teach you when you are free, Phatsa.

631
00:49:40,860 --> 00:49:41,660
Ai.

632
00:49:43,000 --> 00:49:44,860
Can you give me a little more time?

633
00:49:45,260 --> 00:49:46,200
What's the rush?

634
00:49:46,530 --> 00:49:48,760
I haven't finished chatting
with my friends.

635
00:49:48,760 --> 00:49:49,960
But it's been a while.

636
00:49:50,400 --> 00:49:51,800
Just a little longer, OK?

637
00:49:52,900 --> 00:49:53,700
OK.

638
00:50:00,130 --> 00:50:03,910
Hello. I know. I'm getting in the car
right now.

639
00:50:03,910 --> 00:50:07,700
Stop nagging. It was just a moment.

640
00:50:09,790 --> 00:50:13,440
Oh, Phatsa, since you became his,

641
00:50:14,700 --> 00:50:16,990
you really do go left when he says left
and right when he says right.

642
00:50:16,990 --> 00:50:20,240
Honestly, are you in such a rush
to get back

643
00:50:20,320 --> 00:50:21,400
because you can't stand being away
from his pheromones,

644
00:50:21,400 --> 00:50:24,000
or because you can't stand
being away from him?

645
00:50:24,960 --> 00:50:27,660
It's not about that at all.

646
00:50:27,660 --> 00:50:30,520
I'm just afraid his family
will cause a scene again.

647
00:50:32,060 --> 00:50:34,160
I just don't want things to blow up.

648
00:50:35,400 --> 00:50:36,800
What are you laughing at?

649
00:50:37,930 --> 00:50:38,730
I'm leaving.

650
00:50:44,200 --> 00:50:45,200
I'm going to work.

651
00:50:52,730 --> 00:50:53,760
I'm leaving.

652
00:51:01,460 --> 00:51:02,260
Wait.

653
00:51:03,730 --> 00:51:05,330
Where are you rushing off to?

654
00:51:07,400 --> 00:51:09,060
I haven't finished speaking.

655
00:51:11,100 --> 00:51:12,630
I'll come find you tonight.

656
00:51:13,330 --> 00:51:14,630
No need to come.

657
00:51:15,300 --> 00:51:19,300
There's nothing between us anymore.

658
00:51:21,030 --> 00:51:24,860
I also forgave you
for what happened that night.

659
00:51:27,660 --> 00:51:32,860
Let's be clear in the future.

660
00:51:34,030 --> 00:51:36,490
Don't let the life of an ordinary Beta
like me

661
00:51:38,930 --> 00:51:40,730
become more messy than it is now.

662
00:51:46,530 --> 00:51:48,600
Oh, why isn't anyone answering?

663
00:51:50,160 --> 00:51:51,840
Ongsa.

664
00:51:52,260 --> 00:51:54,700
I can't get a car to pick me up. Look.

665
00:51:55,060 --> 00:51:55,860
Let me see.

666
00:51:57,360 --> 00:51:59,760
I called several times
and no one answered.

667
00:52:02,600 --> 00:52:04,300
Nakhin happens to be free.

668
00:52:05,530 --> 00:52:08,000
May I trouble you to take Saengnuea
for me?

669
00:52:09,160 --> 00:52:09,960
May I?

670
00:52:10,760 --> 00:52:13,360
If it's convenient, may I trouble you?

671
00:52:14,530 --> 00:52:15,330
Yes.

672
00:52:22,700 --> 00:52:24,030
I'll head off then, bro.

673
00:52:24,100 --> 00:52:24,900
See you later.

674
00:52:27,600 --> 00:52:28,400
Thank you.

675
00:52:41,960 --> 00:52:42,890
Did you have fun?

676
00:52:44,060 --> 00:52:44,860
Yeah, I did.

677
00:52:47,360 --> 00:52:50,490
But you really shouldn't have asked Nakhin
to pick me up.

678
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:54,130
Ongsa and I haven't finished talking.

679
00:52:54,500 --> 00:52:56,200
Ongsa is a Beta, right?

680
00:52:57,130 --> 00:52:57,930
Yes.

681
00:52:59,960 --> 00:53:02,490
Then invite him to come to our house
next time.

682
00:53:04,660 --> 00:53:05,990
Can I really invite him?

683
00:53:06,930 --> 00:53:09,660
Of course. Isn't he your friend?

684
00:53:10,500 --> 00:53:17,260
Actually, I have another friend
named Saengnuea, who is an Omega.

685
00:53:18,530 --> 00:53:21,100
He taught me a lot about Omegas.

686
00:53:23,300 --> 00:53:24,600
Can I invite him too?

687
00:53:25,860 --> 00:53:29,120
There are still many Alphas who haven't
formed a bond here.

688
00:53:29,860 --> 00:53:31,320
Your friend Saengnuea...

689
00:53:32,900 --> 00:53:34,630
It's best he doesn't come here.

690
00:53:36,400 --> 00:53:38,000
Is it really that dangerous?

691
00:53:39,760 --> 00:53:45,960
If something goes wrong, or an Omega
goes in Heat, they might get bitten.

692
00:53:47,600 --> 00:53:49,400
So it really is quite dangerous.

693
00:54:18,600 --> 00:54:19,400
Hey!

694
00:54:20,900 --> 00:54:21,700
You...

695
00:54:22,930 --> 00:54:24,990
Didn't I say not to get touchy-feely?

696
00:54:32,700 --> 00:54:34,260
Can I hug you?

697
00:54:38,360 --> 00:54:39,460
No.

698
00:54:40,330 --> 00:54:41,990
I just came back from outside.

699
00:54:44,200 --> 00:54:45,560
I'm all hot and sweaty.

700
00:54:53,900 --> 00:54:55,500
But I want to smell you.

701
00:55:04,480 --> 00:55:05,600
No.

702
00:55:13,330 --> 00:55:14,900
Then smell my hand first.

703
00:55:31,730 --> 00:55:32,830
Hey, you!

704
00:55:34,160 --> 00:55:39,810
Why are you licking? Stop! Get out!

705
00:55:42,400 --> 00:55:43,310
Phatsa...

706
00:55:46,360 --> 00:55:47,160
No.

707
00:55:53,200 --> 00:55:54,660
Then give me your clothes.

708
00:56:00,860 --> 00:56:01,660
Clothes...

709
00:56:02,900 --> 00:56:03,760
Clothes?

710
00:56:09,200 --> 00:56:11,200
Take off your shirt and give it to me.

711
00:58:32,060 --> 00:58:34,320
What is he doing?
Why is it taking so long?

712
00:58:39,960 --> 00:58:40,760
Phatsa.

713
00:58:52,430 --> 00:58:53,100
Phatsa.

714
00:59:05,440 --> 00:59:06,240
Phatsa.

715
00:59:21,360 --> 00:59:22,760
I should go take a shower.

716
00:59:29,260 --> 00:59:31,820
Why did you have to fall in love
with a Beta like me?

717
00:59:29,420 --> 00:59:33,160
[In the next episode]

718
00:59:32,160 --> 00:59:33,460
So what if you're a Beta?

719
00:59:33,460 --> 00:59:36,500
Alpha, Omega, or Beta,
aren't we all human in the end?

720
00:59:36,760 --> 00:59:38,220
I don't want to do it today.

721
00:59:38,300 --> 00:59:39,760
Why are you so moody today?

722
00:59:40,500 --> 00:59:41,850
I'm not moody.

723
00:59:42,260 --> 00:59:44,900
Why did you send people
to Nakhun's warehouse?

724
00:59:45,260 --> 00:59:46,800
There's been no damage this time.

725
00:59:46,800 --> 00:59:48,100
I won't report it to the police.

726
00:59:48,100 --> 00:59:49,500
I'll handle this myself.

727
00:59:49,500 --> 00:59:50,830
What exactly happened?

728
00:59:50,930 --> 00:59:52,660
My brother was shot yesterday.

729
00:59:52,930 --> 00:59:53,860
What did you say?

730
01:00:07,610 --> 01:00:11,420
♪ I linger in those beautiful memories ♪

731
01:00:11,450 --> 01:00:14,790
♪ I used to think we were destined ♪

732
01:00:15,110 --> 01:00:16,730
♪ But I also know ♪

733
01:00:16,760 --> 01:00:20,650
♪ that reality isn't like that ♪

734
01:00:20,770 --> 01:00:25,070
♪ I tried so hard to keep you
from leaving ♪

735
01:00:25,090 --> 01:00:28,560
♪ But this broken love
is already shattered ♪

736
01:00:28,580 --> 01:00:31,080
♪ Because I always believed
you would stay ♪

737
01:00:31,080 --> 01:00:34,980
♪ I would give up everything for you ♪

738
01:00:35,160 --> 01:00:37,680
♪ We should have had
the most beautiful future ♪

739
01:00:37,680 --> 01:00:40,660
♪ But there's no result anymore ♪

740
